    <sec id="s2c">
      <title>Strong processivity and high hemi-preference ratio of in vivo human DNMT1 at two inactive X (Xi)-linked loci</title>
      <p>The methylation patterns at the <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="pone.0032225.e052.jpg" mimetype="image"/></inline-formula> and <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="pone.0032225.e053.jpg" mimetype="image"/></inline-formula> loci share many similarities: 77–82% of the CpG sites are fully methylated, whereas only 6–9% are hemimethylated, some of which form a few relatively long runs of hemimethylated dyads (<xref ref-type="table" rid="pone-0032225-t001">Table 1</xref>). Analyses of these two data sets under our HMM also produce similar estimates of the key parameters.</p>
